    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mechanical tension is the direct muscular force applied to the muscle fibers, which is the primary driver for hypertrophy, often achieved through heavy lifting. Metabolic stress, on the other hand, is the accumulation of metabolites like lactate during high-volume, shorter rest periods. Both are important, but mechanical tension is generally considered the most potent stimulus for initiating muscle growth. To optimize, you need a balanced approach that incorporates both heavy, tension-focused work and higher-rep, metabolic stress-inducing sets.",
      "source": "target",
